The paper deals with the concept of DAG-width, which is a parameter related to directed acyclic graphs (DAGs). This makes categories related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS) likely candidates. The paper also involves complexity theory, as it proves that deciding DAG-width is PSPACE-complete, which suggests categories related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG) as possible choices. Finally, the paper deals with graph theory, which makes categories related to graph theory (cs.GT) a likely option as well.
